rComments: I took women and religions with prof Goldenberg, and I was scared considering I don't know anything about religion. Naomi made the class super interesting and always kept us engaged! She may be little but she has a BIG personality, which I love. Attendance is a big part of the grade, so don't skip!!

Professor Goldenberg was an exceptional prof. She does not like students to be late, and there is no talking allowed. She definitely made a 7-10 worth it. There were quizzes every week, a midterm in class (questions were given ahead of time) and a final take home. Definitely recommend!

Dr. Goldenberg is simply amazing. She cares for her students success (1 midterm that is in-class but we were given the questions a week ahead + 1 take home exam). Small quizzes every week, but they were easy. Go to class, take good notes (no technology allowed), and you will succeed.

Hands down the worst prof I've ever had the displeasure of meeting. She was rude, demeaning, and most of all completely useless when asked a question. Any lateness will be met with yelling and a childish disruption from the professor. Honestly I could not be more disappointed with the class and the prof.
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Favourite prof at uOttawa; so knowledgeable and truly at the top of her field. Weekly quizzes about the previous lecture are an easy grade booster, which is great since her midterm and final were quite challenging. She loves class participation and never fails to let everyone have their turn to speak. Highly recommend!

Absolutely the best professor I have ever had. I don't think i will ever experience something as hard as her class, but it truly was fascinating. I would take one of her classes again in a heartbeat. She is obviously extremely knowledgeable. She uses a lot of textbooks, but they are easy to find and not overly expensive. All online too!
This is honestly the best professor Ive ever had and this class is a truly inspiring class. EASY ELECTIVE!!!
It is so difficult because no idea about the exam, not allowed to use any tech and nothing will post Black board. Too crazy one.

This prof is amazing! She doe not allow any sorts of technology and will call you out if she sees you using it. She gets to know your name which made me feel like a person and not a number in the class. Participation matters as there is quizzes every class and there were 2 long papers. Put in the work and you'll ace! She also doesn't post on BB.

Fabulous professor and a great person all around, definitely one of my favourite professors throughout my 3 years at university. Easy assignments and extra credit opportunities to boost your grade, gives helpful hints on take home midterms and exams that lead you in the right direction. Will always recommend courses taught by her.
Hands down the best professor I have ever had.

Goldenberg is my favourite professor in my four years of uni. Engaging lectures, and tons of extra-credit opportunity if you feel nervous about the thick course material. Exams are take-home, but every question on them was discussed in class, so it's not a shock. If you participate, she remembers your name and appreciates/respects you. Recommended.

Wonderful wonderful woman with very easy to follow lectures and frequent reviews. Participation is tons of marks (done by super easy quizzes you'll get perfect on if you attend class) and exams were both take home (again super easy if you attend class and take down notes). TAKE THIS COURSE- easy A but also very interesting
If you want to learn something about your potential, Prof. Goldenberg will help you find it.

Professor Goldenberg is everything you want from a university professor. She is funny, engaging and extremely knowledgeable in her field. My class with her was easily my favourite of the year and I left every class feeling like I actually learned something. This class does require work, but it is well worth it for a prof this great.

She's a bit eccentric but her lectures are excellent - hilarious, engaging, and she gives you most if not all the information for the exams (which are take homes). She does take attendance but honestly her class is such a delight that you'll want to be there anyway. Plus, she's really sweet and wonderful in person.

Naomi Goldenberg is a gem, easily one of my favourite professors at uOttawa. Her instructions are straight forward and assigned readings are actually interesting. Her lectures are fresh and fun, weekly quizzes are a breeze (just go to class, pay attention and you're golden). Signed up for SRS3165 simply because she was teaching it.

You don't REALLY have to read the books, just google the answers. She is really not easy  to get a hold of and her expectations are super unclear, but overall Iits a good class. I thought I was going to fail the first midterm but I did really well.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'So many papers', 'Beware of pop quizzes']

rComments: No electronic devices allowed, very unclear about the papers and exams. Quiz every class. The exam was very long and difficult. Didn't even get the chance to finish. Plus requires 4 books and other articles on blackboard. She is very rude to the students and doesn't respect their opinions. Seems like she doesn't care. I was very disappointed.

On the first day of class, she tells you that if you are not prepared to work, you should drop the class. This is true. Not uncommon to have 300 pages of reading per week.  But she's worth it. Everything you could ever want in the University experience.  Seriously mind blowing, and if you do the work- the marks are there.

Unbelievably difficult midterms &final. Midterm was five 5-7 page papers written in class in 3 hours, it was the most difficult midterm I've ever done in my life. Classes are long&boring, supposed to be a gender&religion course, instead it's mostly a feminist course. Rude, doesn't allow technology, can never get a question in before she cuts u off
teacherRatingTags: ['Beware of pop quizzes', 'Tough grader', 'So many papers']

rComments: Goldenberg is absolutely amazing. Her credentials are unreal, and her lectures reflect that. She's engaging, inspiring and over all an incredible professor. She has a sense of humor, and is direct (which some students don't like) but I think she's brilliant. I've taken as many classes as I can with her. I HIGHLY recommend. She's Ottawa's best.

Marking depends on your TA and their marking assistants, if any. Midterm and final are huge papers (20 and 30 pgs double spaced respectively). Class notes and readings are a must when writing these papers and secondaryoutside sources, not so much. Takes attendance in the form of quizzes. Oh, and no electronics are permitted during class lectures.

The most incredible personality that I met at OttawaU. Took her class as elective. She is a fascinating human being. Great intellectual power and acuity, great knowledge and deep understanding. It was a pleasure and a honor to even meet such a marvelous and distinct individual, not to say about listening to her great speeches for 3 h each week.
Fair grader. Really interesting lectures that are fun to participate in. Enjoyed going to class. You must go to class as there are participation marks and no slides or notes given.

Amazing teacher, keeps people awake for sure. Very distinctive voice. A lot of reading if you actually do it. Hate to do this to you, and you will remember this when she does it. She pronounces "human" as "uman" no "h" now you know....
Extremely engaging. Super interesting content and she explains it well and you can tell she's interested. She's humorous and sarcastic. Loved the class!

Blatant disrespect for people who have differing views on the world. She talk over students and insults them. In my class she actually pointed out a student with a learning disability and shamed her. I would not recommend her to anyone.

This woman is my idol. She is incredibly dynamic, interesting, funny, and fashionable! Required textbook use is low (use the ones on reserve at the library), mandatory attendance + evals are take-home. NOTE: this is not a bird course though! I received an A+ but worked my ass off for it. Low stress because of take-homes but not easy. Recommend.

Prof. Goldenberg is AMAZING! Her lectures are super interesting and her energy is entirely compelling. She does tend to get sidetracked easily, but quite frankly it makes her more interesting. Exams are easy (basically take-home essay-style questions). I only did the readings required for the questions given right at exam time. Super nice and funny

She goes on random tangents alot! Like, the amount of useful notes you take in a 3 hour class is less than you would a 1.5 hour!So just... know how to filter what she says. but interesting!Extremely feminist and her bias leaks into her teaching.

Definitely an energetic prof but also definitely a little nuts.  Total boot-camp feminist.  Once told class that high-heels were sexy because the heel was a phallic juxtaposition to the feminine body.  Overall OK though.
Best professor at Ottawa u! You'll never be bored in her class. Ever.
really funny

Ottawa U is so lucky to have her. greatest professor ever! the classes fly by, the material was really interesting, there were lots of videos and guest speakers. she is very likeable! i highly recommend her! naomi rules!!!!!!!!

FABULOUS teacher. amazing speaker teaching an interesting class, expectations are clear. we have had lots of guest speakers so far which is nice. many of my friends knew who Naomi was by reputation, and said how I was lucky to have her as a teacher. they were right! very cool lady.

Excellent teacher.  The material is interesting and she might be the only teacher who can really work an 8:30am class.  The material was interesting and she is an excellent professor.  It was very clear what would be on the midterm, she gave a comprehensive review and it was exactly what she said it would be.  I would recommend her to anyone.
She's a bombshell. I hate three hour classes first thing in the morning, but she can really keep you interested because of her terrific teaching style. Definitely a teacher I'd recommend.

Fabulous professor.I loved this class. She is such an ethusiastic professor that loves what she is teaching and knows what she is talking about. She recognizes students and tries to learn everyone's name (and did well). Absolutely take a class with her! Exams aren't hard, final was a take home. I loved everything about this class.
small woman, massive presence.

She talks an awful lot, but is tolerable.  notices if you were away which is crazy bc she doesnt take attendance. I give her props for her slim figure and hot shoes. Oh and take home exams and cheat sheets rule her classroom.
I thought she was great!  Always interesting to listen to, and her midterms and tests weren't too hard.  I really enjoyed the class.
She is possibly my favorite prof. ever, so funny, I can actually stay awake in the early class. Sounds exactly like Karen from Will & Grace.

She is amazing.  Her wealth of knowledge delights her students as she provokes discussions and thoughts that are interesting and enlightening.  Her style may not be for everybody, but I just love her!

This prof is absolutely amazing and with her academic background, U of O is lucky to have her.  She is lively, well-spoken, and chooses interesting readings for the course.  Her takehome exams are extremely fair, just argue your point using references.
Lunatic. Seriously, she should be teaching elementary school.
